            "longDescription"   : "All TI LaunchPads follow standard BoosterPack (BP) locations to ensure compatibility with BoosterPack peripherals. Sites 1 and 2 on this LaunchPad features standard locations for ADC inputs, DAC_OUT, UART3, SPI0, SPI2, I2C0, I2C1, various EPWM Channels, LIN1, LIN2, MCAN0, MCAN1, SDFM0, SDFM1, GPIOs, and various PR1_PRU0 and PR1_PRU1 GPIOs. Note that the standard BoosterPack mode signal hardware connections are enabled as part of this EVM sysconfig file. Secondary signals for specific alternative BoosterPack modes will require muxing in order to route to the BoosterPack headers. The alternative BoosterPack modes are configured using the BP_MUX_SW_S1 and BP_MUX_SW_S0 signals, which are outputs from the I2C-controlled IO Expander. The IO Expander can be configured using the IO Expander module under the 'Software' tab in SysConfig. \n\n![](../source/sysconfig/board/.meta/images/lp-am261_boosterpack.png) \n\n **BP_MUX_SW_S1** | **BP_MUX_SW_S0** | **BoosterPack Mux Mode**         \n------------------|------------------|----------------------------------\n       0/LOW      |       0/LOW      | Standard LaunchPad BoosterPack   \n       0/LOW      |      1/HIGH      | Servo Motor Control BoosterPacks \n      1/HIGH      |       0/LOW      | IO-LINK BoosterPack              \n      1/HIGH      |      1/HIGH      | C2000 DRVx BoosterPack           ",
